column5: Has anyone stayed at West Point Cove Resort on Pelican Lake? If so, could you give me your opinion of the resort and lake for fishing.

Nice Place. Reasonable. Good People. Not a full service place. Only 2 cabins - one new, one old. New one is very nice (Eagle's Nest). Nice fish cleaning shack. We trailer to Deception Bay (Lac Seul) on most days, but the fishing on Pelican is pretty good. I recommend it.
